    <description>Tartube is a GUI front-end for youtube-dlc, youtube-dl and other compatible video downloaders.

It is partly based on youtube-dl-gui and is written in Python 3 / Gtk 3. Tartube runs on MS Windows, Linux, BSD and MacOS.

**32 bit users**: Due to an error (see issue: https://github.com/axcore/tartube#doesn-t-work-on-32-bit-windows), Tartube is no longer updated for the 32 bit version. if you need 32bit please install version: **2.3.332**

**Please Note**: This is an automatically updated package. If you find it is out of date by more than a day or two, please contact the maintainer(s) and let them know the package is no longer updating correctly.</description>
    <summary>A GUI front-end for youtube-dl, partly based on youtube-dl-gui and written in Python 3 / Gtk 3</summary>
    <releaseNotes>
# MAJOR NEW FEATURES
- Downloads from YouTube now require that you install Deno or some other compatible JavaScript runtime. The MS Windows installer includes a copy of Deno; users on Linux should install Deno using their normal package manager. Tartube is now configured by default to specify Deno in all video downloads; you can modify this behaviour, if you like, by clicking Edit &gt; System preferences... &gt; Downloaders &gt; JavaScript
- For some time, the alarm that should be played when a livestream started (if you've enabled that behaviour) did not play, because the Python playsound module has been abandoned and is not available to most users. Tartube now supports the playsound3 module instead; it's included in the MS Windows installer
# MINOR NEW FEATURES
- Added an option to disable the monospace fonts in the Output tab, for the benefit of a small number of users for whom the fonts are illegible. To set it, click Edit &gt; System preferences &gt; Output &gt; Output tab, and select 'Disable monospace fonts in the Output tab' (Git #[766](https://github.com/axcore/tartube/issues/766))
- The Output tab (and Classic Mode tab) now show the time at which a download finished, which is useful for scheduled downloads (Git #[783](https://github.com/axcore/tartube/issues/783))
- In the Videos tab, you can now mark multiple videos as downloaded (or not downloaded), for example by right-clicking a channel and selecting 'Channel contents &gt; Mark as downloaded'. You can also select multiple videos, and then right-click them before selecting 'Mark videos &gt; Downloaded'. This feature should be used with caution (Git #[783](https://github.com/axcore/tartube/issues/783))
- When updating yt-dlp, you can now update using the nightly build, instead of the main release (if you want to). This works on all systems, but only for PIP installs (so it's available for all MS Windows users). To enable it, click Edit &gt; System preferences... &gt; Downloaders &gt; Forks, and enable the 'Install nightly build' option
# MAJOR FIXES
- Fixed a crash when preparing yt-dlp download options (Git #[778](https://github.com/axcore/tartube/issues/778))
- Added a workaround for a crash observed when re-downloading a video; more detail is required for a permanent fix (Git #[779](https://github.com/axcore/tartube/issues/779))
- In the Videos tab, the search feature did not work when the 'Authors' button was selected. Another user reported crashes when using the search feature. Fixed (Git #[761](https://github.com/axcore/tartube/issues/761), #[784](https://github.com/axcore/tartube/issues/784))
- In the download options window, in the Files &gt; Cookies tab, the entry box above the 'Browser' dropdown box was not updated, when the dropdown box itself was updated. Fixed (Git #[774](https://github.com/axcore/tartube/issues/774))
- Also in the Files &gt; Cookies tab, if the user de-selected 'Do not load cookies from this browser (having earlier selected it), then '--no-cookies-from-browser' was added to the yt-dlp command. Fixed (Git #[768](https://github.com/axcore/tartube/issues/768))
- Also in the Files &gt; Cookies tab, when the user selected 'Firefox' in the 'Browser' dropdown box, and then reset that box, and then clicked 'Apply', the 'Firefox' option was automatically re-enabled. Fixed (Git #[776](https://github.com/axcore/tartube/issues/776))
# MINOR FIXES
- In the Classic Mode tab, when the user changed the 'Download in this format' box to 'Convert to this form', the choice was not remembered. Fixed (Git #[759](https://github.com/axcore/tartube/issues/759))
- Minor updates to the MS Windows installer (Git #[760](https://github.com/axcore/tartube/issues/760))
- Updated MacOS installation instructions (Git #[764](https://github.com/axcore/tartube/issues/764))
# 
**Full changelog:** [https://raw.githubusercontent.com/axcore/tartube/master/CHANGES](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/axcore/tartube/master/CHANGES)</releaseNotes>
